transcripts.text: Everyone counts, still at the census.  We're here with Team AOT to help folks get counted in the census.  This only happens once every 10 years, so the funding for the next 10 years is predicated upon people getting involved with it.  This is a process that helps the federal government know how much money to send us for our schools, for our parks and our playgrounds, for community centers, and a slew of other things.  It's vitally important that we all do our duty and get counted.  We know that, especially in communities like ours in Queens, For a lot of people that are living with in basements, in unregulated apartments, or if you're too young to be registered to vote, every single person deserves to get counted so that our federal government is giving us the resources that we need.
